{'id_' : 'eu|funeral_en_US_dedes|euFUN|Key0800|title', 'text' : 'Funeral Hymns'}
{'id_' : 'eu|funeral_en_US_dedes|euFUN|Key0800|poet', 'text' : 'By John the Monk (of Damascus).'}
{'id_' : 'eu|funeral_en_US_dedes|euFUN|Key0801|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 1.'}
{'id_' : 'eu|funeral_en_US_dedes|euFUN|Key0801|text', 'text' : 'Which of life's pleasures remains free of sorrow? Which earthly glory is permanent? All this is fainter than a shadow, all more illusory than a dream. In a single moment, death succeeds them all. O Christ, grant rest to those whom You have taken, in the light of Your face and in the sweetness of Your handsomeness, as the One who loves humanity.'}
{'id_' : 'eu|funeral_en_US_dedes|euFUN|Key0802|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 2.'}
{'id_' : 'eu|funeral_en_US_dedes|euFUN|Key0802|text', 'text' : 'A flower withers and a dream passes, and likewise every human being disintegrates. Then at the sound of the trumpet, as if in an earthquake, all the dead will rise to meet You, O Christ God. We pray You will then place the spirit of those whom You have taken from us in the dwellings of Your Saints, O Christ.'}
{'id_' : 'eu|funeral_en_US_dedes|euFUN|Key0803|title', 'text' : 'Another Extra Hymn.'}
{'id_' : 'eu|funeral_en_US_dedes|euFUN|Key0803|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 2.'}
{'id_' : 'eu|funeral_en_US_dedes|euFUN|Key0803|text', 'text' : 'Alas! Such agony afflicts a soul when it is separated from its body. Alas! How it weeps then, but there is no one to have mercy on it. It turns its eyes towards the Angels and prays to no avail. It reaches for other people, but there is no one who can help. Therefore, my beloved brethren, let us realize how short is our life, and let us pray to Christ to grant repose to the departed, and great mercy to our souls.'}
{'id_' : 'eu|funeral_en_US_dedes|euFUN|Key0804|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 3.'}
{'id_' : 'eu|funeral_en_US_dedes|euFUN|Key0804|text', 'text' : 'Vanity is everything human, which after death exists no more. Wealth does not remain, glory does not go with us; for when death arrives, all these disappear. Therefore let us cry to Christ the immortal King, "Grant rest to those departed from us, there where glad are all who have their dwelling in You."'}
{'id_' : 'eu|funeral_en_US_dedes|euFUN|Key0805|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 4.'}
{'id_' : 'eu|funeral_en_US_dedes|euFUN|Key0805|melody', 'text' : 'You have given.'}
{'id_' : 'eu|funeral_en_US_dedes|euFUN|Key0805|text', 'text' : 'Frightening indeed, and quite so, is the mystery known as death, how a soul then is forcibly * separated from its frame, parting from its body; * severed is that union, which is most natural and innate, * by Your divine will, O Lover of mankind. * And therefore we entreat You grant to the departed eternal rest, * where the saints and the righteous dwell, * O our God and the Giver of life.'}
{'id_' : 'eu|funeral_en_US_dedes|euFUN|Key0806|title', 'text' : 'Another Extra Hymn.'}
{'id_' : 'eu|funeral_en_US_dedes|euFUN|Key0806|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 4.'}
{'id_' : 'eu|funeral_en_US_dedes|euFUN|Key0806|text', 'text' : 'Where are all those worldly attachments? Where are the imaginings of things that do not last? Where is the gold, where the silver? Where is the flood and fuss of assistants and servants? All of this is dust and ashes, all just a shadow. Nevertheless, come let us say to the immortal King, "Lord, grant Your eternal good things to those departed from us, and give them rest in unending blessedness."'}
{'id_' : 'eu|funeral_en_US_dedes|euFUN|Key0807|mode', 'text' : 'Mode pl. 1.'}
{'id_' : 'eu|funeral_en_US_dedes|euFUN|Key0807|text', 'text' : 'I remembered how the Prophet once said: "I am but dust and ashes"; and then I looked into the graves and saw the naked bones, and in turn I exclaimed: "Who can tell, which one was a king, which one a soldier, rich or poor, a righteous man or a sinner?" Nevertheless, O Lord, grant that Your servants may rest with the righteous, in Your love for humanity.'}
{'id_' : 'eu|funeral_en_US_dedes|euFUN|Key0808|mode', 'text' : 'Mode pl. 2.'}
{'id_' : 'eu|funeral_en_US_dedes|euFUN|Key0808|text', 'text' : 'Your creative command was my beginning and real existence; for wishing to construct me as a living creature from both visible and invisible natures, You fashioned my body from earth, and You gave me a soul by Your divine and life-giving breath. Therefore, O Savior, give rest to Your servants, in the land of the living, where the righteous dwell.'}
{'id_' : 'eu|funeral_en_US_dedes|euFUN|Key0809|mode', 'text' : 'Grave Mode.'}
{'id_' : 'eu|funeral_en_US_dedes|euFUN|Key0809|melody', 'text' : 'No longer are we barred.'}
{'id_' : 'eu|funeral_en_US_dedes|euFUN|Key0809|text', 'text' : 'O Savior and Life-giver, to those You transferred * from this fleeting life, grant rest, as they cry out, * "Glory to You, O Lord."'}
{'id_' : 'eu|funeral_en_US_dedes|euFUN|Key0810|title', 'text' : 'Another Extra Hymn.'}
{'id_' : 'eu|funeral_en_US_dedes|euFUN|Key0810|mode', 'text' : 'Grave Mode.'}
{'id_' : 'eu|funeral_en_US_dedes|euFUN|Key0810|text', 'text' : 'In the beginning, when You fashioned man in Your image and likeness, You put him in Paradise to have dominion over Your creation. But by the envy of the devil, man was deceived; and he ate the fruit and thus became a transgressor of Your commandments. Therefore, O Lord, You sentenced him to return to the earth, from which he had been taken, and to pray for repose.'}
{'id_' : 'eu|funeral_en_US_dedes|euFUN|Key0811|mode', 'text' : 'Mode pl. 4.'}
{'id_' : 'eu|funeral_en_US_dedes|euFUN|Key0811|text', 'text' : 'I grieve and I lament when I think about death, and when I see the beauty, which God made for us in His image, lying formless in the grave, without glory and unsightly. Amazing! What is this mystery that happened to us? How were we given over to decay and coupled with death? Indeed, as it is written, this is all by the command of God, who grants repose to those who have passed away.'}
{'id_' : 'eu|funeral_en_US_dedes|euFUN|Key0812|mode', 'text' : 'Mode pl. 4.'}
{'id_' : 'eu|funeral_en_US_dedes|euFUN|Key0812|text', 'text' : 'O Lord, Your death gave rise to immortality; for if You had not been enclosed in a tomb, then Paradise would not have been opened. Therefore grant repose to the departed, in Your love for humanity.'}
{'id_' : 'eu|funeral_en_US_dedes|euFUN|Key0813|mode', 'text' : 'Mode pl. 4.'}
{'id_' : 'eu|funeral_en_US_dedes|euFUN|Key0813|text', 'text' : 'O pure Virgin, you are the gate of the Logos, and the Mother of our God. Pray for our salvation.'}
{'id_' : 'eu|funeral_en_US_dedes|euFUN|Key0900|title', 'text' : 'The Beatitudes'}
